![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/2dadeb36-0c42-4f26-84cd-88d5701e335d/e387.jpg?format=original)

This week, the hosts revisit _Judge Dredd_ (1995) for its 30th anniversary! With Sylvester Stallone behind the visor, this cult classic aimed to bring the 2000 AD icon to life—complete with oversized armor, dystopian chaos, and questionable comedy relief. But beyond the explosions and one-liners, the crew dives into the film’s deeper themes: authoritarianism, identity, and the cost of absolute justice. Was _Judge Dredd_ ahead of its time, or just a stylish misfire with a killer helmet? **Three decades later, we put the law on trial.**

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

